# Architecture Handbook Reminder

After completing any major architectural decision, remind the user:

> "This is a good point to create the next Architecture Handbook document.
> Save it to: ~/Documents/AI-Platform-Architecture-Notes/
> Suggested filename: [next number]-[Topic]-Architecture.docx"

## What Triggers a Reminder

A major architectural decision includes any of the following:

- Choosing or changing a technology (vector DB, LLM, framework, cloud service)
- Designing a new abstraction layer or interface
- Implementing a new design pattern across the codebase
- Completing a new Terraform module for a GCP service
- Wiring a new CI/CD pipeline or adding a quality gate
- Making a significant infrastructure decision (networking, IAM, scaling)

